article.description: Kahlil Felder had 33 points, six assists and five steals on Friday night and Oakland led by double digits throughout the second half to beat Wright State 89-63.
article.headline: Felder scores 33, Oakland beats Wright State 89-63
article.linkText: Felder scores 33, Oakland beats Wright State 89-63
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Kahlil Felder had 33 points, six assists and five steals on Friday night and Oakland led by double digits throughout the second half to beat Wright State 89-63. The Golden Grizzlies put it away with a 23-6 run that ended at 80-50 with 5:41 to play. Oakland (14-8, 6-3 Horizon) won its third in a row and pulled a game behind second-place Wright State (13-9, 7-2) in the league standings. Felder was 11 of 17 from the field, 3 of 6 from 3-point range and 8 of 9 from the foul line. The nation's third-leading scorer improved to 25.6 points per game. Martez Walker added 19 points and Percy Gibson scored 12. The Grizzlies never trailed, opened to a 25-9 lead and went into the half up 41-26. Mark Alstork led the Raiders with 10 points.
